## Description
Implement a GitHub GraphQL API client service for fetching user contribution data.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] GraphQL client with authentication
- [ ] Rate limiting implementation (5000 points/hour)
- [ ] Error handling with retry logic
- [ ] Support for pagination
- [ ] Comprehensive logging

## GraphQL Query to Implement
```graphql
query($username: String!, $after: String) {
  user(login: $username) {
    login
    name
    avatarUrl
    publicRepos: repositories(privacy: PUBLIC) {
      totalCount
    }
    pullRequests(first: 50, after: $after, orderBy: {field: CREATED_AT, direction: DESC}) {
      nodes {
        title
        url
        createdAt
        merged
        state
        repository {
          name
          owner { login }
          isPrivate
          collaborators { totalCount }
        }
      }
      pageInfo {
        hasNextPage
        endCursor
      }
    }
  }
}

Technical Details

Use axios or node-fetch for HTTP requests
Implement exponential backoff for retries
Token validation and error handling
TypeScript interfaces for response data

Test Cases

 Successful user data fetch
 Rate limit handling
 Invalid user handling
 Network error recovery
 Pagination functionality

Dependencies: Repository structure setup
Estimated Effort: 3 days

